<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,845,1043]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Ten species are included in the 
<taxonomicName box="[509,639,846,869]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costiniceps">
<emphasis box="[509,639,846,869]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Costiniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Complex: 
<taxonomicName box="[782,942,846,869]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costiniceps">
<emphasis box="[782,942,846,869]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. costiniceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1139,845,869]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cherylbarrae">
<emphasis box="[957,1139,845,869]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. cherylbarrae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1307,845,869]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buscintilla">
<emphasis box="[1154,1307,845,869]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. buscintilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scintillapicta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. scintillapicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[244,370,881,904]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mintrita">
<emphasis box="[244,370,881,904]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. mintrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[385,542,881,904]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">
<emphasis box="[385,542,881,904]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. amazonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[558,746,880,904]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scintillamima">
<emphasis box="[558,746,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. scintillamima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[762,923,880,904]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scintillarca">
<emphasis box="[762,923,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. scintillarca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1121,880,904]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanoscintilla">
<emphasis box="[939,1121,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. nanoscintilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1186,1353,880,904]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiana">
<emphasis box="[1186,1353,880,904]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. colombiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These are medium sized species (ca. 
<quantity box="[491,657,914,938]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.38" metricValueMax="1.51" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="1.38" valueMax="1.51" valueMin="1.25">1.25–1.51 mm</quantity>
), which have a large pronotal scintilla. The pronotum has a macula or fascia in some species, but is dark, unicolorous in others. The male genitalia are stout in this complex, and have a basic plan similarity, with the main-piece, distal piece, and parameres together forming a more or less cup shape; the gonopore bearing flagellum is short and 'inside' the cup (e.g., 
<figureCitation box="[883,1020,1018,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 26" captionStartId="89.[151,264,1726,1749]" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 26. Aedeagi of holotypes." pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Figs. 
<number box="[945,1020,1018,1042]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="25.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="25.0">25–26</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
